ZH: 我不能袒护你的错误行为。
EN: I cannot condone your wrongful behavior.

ZH: 他一直袒护他的朋友，不管他们做了什么错事。
EN: He always shields his friends, no matter what wrongdoings they commit.

ZH: 妈妈总是袒护我，即使我犯了错误。
EN: Mom always protects me, even when I make mistakes.

ZH: 这个公司内部有许多袒护坏人的行为。
EN: There are many acts of shielding culprits within this company.

ZH: 我无法袒护你对他人的攻击行为。
EN: I cannot defend your actions of attacking others.

ZH: 我警告你不要袒护那些欺凌者。
EN: I warn you not to support those bullies.

ZH: 上司袒护他的下属，不惩罚他们的错误。
EN: The boss shields his subordinates and does not punish them for their mistakes.

ZH: 老师不应该袒护学生的不良行为。
EN: A teacher should not condone students' bad behavior.

ZH: 我会袒护我的朋友，因为我知道他是无辜的。
EN: I will stand up for my friend because I know he is innocent.

ZH: 我不能袒护那个贪污犯。
EN: I cannot offer protection to that corrupt criminal.

ZH: 我不愿袒护你在这次事故中的责任。
EN: I am unwilling to shield you from the responsibility in this accident.

ZH: 警方袒护了那名犯罪嫌疑人。
EN: The police covered up for the criminal suspect.

ZH: 我袒护你并不代表你可以一直做错事。
EN: Just because I defend you doesn't mean you can keep doing wrong things.

ZH: 这里有一种文化现象，人们更倾向于袒护有权势的人。
EN: There is a cultural phenomenon here where people tend to protect those in power.

ZH: 他在团队中袒护了一个明显不称职的成员。
EN: He shielded an obviously incompetent member within the team.

ZH: 请不要袒护不义之人。
EN: Please do not condone the unjust.

ZH: 我会袒护我的真诚朋友。
EN: I will stand by my true friends.

ZH: 领导们经常袒护纪律松散的员工。
EN: Leaders often shield undisciplined employees.

ZH: 老板不袒护员工的错误，而是要求他们负责。
EN: The boss does not condone employees' mistakes but holds them accountable.

ZH: 我不能为你的过错袒护。
EN: I cannot shield you from your faults.
